<H3> <TI>   UNA-UNSO Issues Statement on Members' Arrest </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNA-UNSO Issues Statement on Members' Arrest </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205183094 Kiev UT-1 Television Network in Ukrainian 1600 
GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205183094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UT-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [No video available] </F>
  [Text] The Ukrainian National Assembly [UNA] has issued a 
statement that says, in particular: "While none of the Crimean 
separatists have been made liable for violating Ukrainian laws, 
attempting to separate the Ukrainian lands and kindling 
interethnic enmity, some Ukrainian patriots are in prison." The 
statement points to a repeated arrest of Valeriy Bobrovych, a 
leading member of the UNSO [Ukrainian National Self-Defense--the 
paramilitary wing of the UNA] territorial command in Lvov, who 
had arrived in Kiev for an operation after sustaining an injury 
in Abkhazia. 

</TEXT>

