<H3> <TI>   Rail Official: No Orders for Military Transport to Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rail Official: No Orders for Military Transport to Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2305094394 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0500 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2305094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In connection with Russian mass media reports about 
repositioning of the Ukrainian military units and formations in 
the direction of the Crimean Autonomous Republic, the Ukrainian 
Railroads press service issued a statement. Among others, the 
statement said that over the past 10 days, it received no orders 
for transporting military loads, personnel, and military 
equipment in the direction of the Crimea from the Ukrainian 
Defense Ministry and National Guards. 

</TEXT>

