<H3> <TI>   Ukraine Premier Leaves for Moscow; Accords To Be Signed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ukraine Premier Leaves for Moscow; Accords To Be Signed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305110194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1053 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 23 May TASS -- Acting Ukrainian Prime Minister 
Yukhym Zvyahilskiy left for Moscow on Monday [23 May] to meet 
his Russian counterpart Viktor Chernomyrdin and discuss the 
Crimean crisis and Russian-Ukrainian relations. 
  It became known to tass that it is planned to draft a 
package 
of agreements to be later signed by presidents of Russia and 
Ukraine. 
  The meeting between the prime ministers was agreed upon in a 
telephone conversation of Boris Yeltsin and Leonid Kravchuk on 
19 May. 

</TEXT>

