<F P=102>   LD2105205294 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1800 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tajik military subunits have been withdrawn from the 
collective peacekeeping forces in Tajikistan, Colonel General 
Valeriy Patrikeyev, commander of the collective peacekeeping 
forces in Tajikistan, said on Saturday. 
  At the same time, the commander reported that the term for 
the presence of peacekeeping forces in the republic had been 
extended until 31 December. 
  At present, the total number of CIS peacekeeping forces is 
9,000 men less than previously planned. The commander expressed 
concern that Kazakhstan had not yet allocated its own battalion 
to join the forces. 

</TEXT>

