  [Text] Russian president Boris Nikolayevich Yeltsin today 
answered journalists' questions concerning the situation in 
Crimea. 
  [Begin Yeltsin recording] I spoke with Ukraine President 
Kravchuk yesterday. We discussed these issues. I gave a 
warning and he promised that Ukraine will not use any force 
whatsoever in Crimea. He promised me this, and we hope that the 
president, a respectable person, will keep his promise. Crimea 
is a sovereign republic and it has a right to make its own 
decisions. And it will make those decisions--but it is vital 
that neither we nor Ukraine should interfere. [end recording] 

