<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 21 TASS -- A new Russian negotiator to 
the talks with the Chechen Republic will be appointed in the 
near future, Russian Presidential Administration Chief of Staff 
Sergey Filatov said on Saturday. 
  Filatov made it clear that the removal of Vice-Prime 
Minister 
Sergey Shakhray from the post of nationalities minister is 
connected with the need to find ways to enhance relations 
between Russia and the Chechen Republic. 
  Shakhray had a firm position at the talks, insisting on 
early 
elections in the Chechen Republic and participation of the 
Chechen opposition in the talks as a pre-condition. 
  Filatov confirmed Russian President Boris Yeltsin's 
intention 
to meet with Chechen President Dzhokhar Dudayev in the near 
future. 

</TEXT>

