<F P=102>   LD2305152094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1436 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature: by correspondents </F>
Igor Porshnev, Vitaliy Trubetskoy, and others] 
  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk hoped that the 
Ukrainian and Crimean parliamentary delegations which would meet 
on Tuesday [24 May], would find a solution to the Crimean issue. 
  However, the only possible way is not to alter the status of 
Crimea or the territorial integrity of Ukraine, Kravchuk told 
journalists on Sunday when he was present at a Cossack 
celebration in the city of Pervomaisk in the Nikolayevsk Region. 
  Kravchuk emphasized that territorial integrity was the 
borderline which must not be violated. This holds for Crimea as 
well, Kravchuk stressed. 
  He also said that the crisis could be solved as soon as the 
Crimean parliament cancels its decision to reinstate the 1992 
constitution which introduces dual citizenship and relations 
with Kiev based on agreements. 

</TEXT>

