<H3> <TI>   Russian Industrialists' Union President Arrives in Dushanbe </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Industrialists' Union President Arrives in Dushanbe </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305195094 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1811 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The main purpose of the visit to Tajikistan by the 
President of the Russian Union of Industrialists and 
Entrepreneurs is participation in a congress of the Tajik Union 
of Science and Industry on Wednesday [25 May]. He disclosed 
this to INTERFAX on Monday in Dushanbe where he arrived as the 
head of a 23 person delegation. 
  Volskiy thinks the contacts of industrialists are now 
extremely necessary for both Russia and Tajikistan because there 
is a burning need to discuss further cooperation and begin 
seeking a way out of the crisis. "We cannot help it, because we 
would find life difficult without each other," Volskiy said. 
  Asked about the expected results of the working visit 
Volskiy 
said an agreement with the Tajik union was drafted and Russian 
businessmen would gladly sign it, if Tajik colleagues approved 
it. 
  The visit will last till 26 May. On Tuesday Volskiy is to 
meet the chairman of parliament Emomali Rakhmonov. 

</TEXT>

