<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Troops Increase Control in Ingushetia-Ossetia Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Troops Increase Control in Ingushetia-Ossetia Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305163894 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1116 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 23 May -- Mobile groups of Russian 
troops have stepped up control over the safety strip between 
North Ossetia and Ingushetia. ITAR-TASS learned on Monday that 
this had been done in line with an instruction by Vladimir 
Lozovoy, the head of the interim administration. 
  In the meantime, a wide-scale "transport" operation aimed to 
strengthen the state of emergency regime is under way in the 
zone where the regime is in force. It envisages thorough 
check-ups of vehicles, trains, train stations, and airports. It 
was reported that dozens of fire-arms, hand-grenades, various 
rounds of ammunition, and drugs had been confiscated from 
passengers over the past three days. 
  Information obtained by ITAR-TASS from military sources 
makes 
it possible to conclude that the situation in the North Ossetian 
rayons where the state of emergency regime is in force until 31 
May remains relatively calm. No night shellings or attacks on 
army or militia posts or interethnic conflicts have been 
registered here in the past 24 hours. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

