<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kostikov Appeals to Residents </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kostikov Appeals to Residents </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305175794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1725 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 23 TASS -- Russian presidential spokesman 
Vyacheslav Kostikov called on the citizens of North Ossetia and 
Ingushetia to resist provocations aimed at thwarting the process 
of conflict settlement in the region. 
  In a statement issued on Monday, Kostikov said that 
extremists have lately stepped up their activity in the war zone 
in North Ossetia and Ingushetia. Violence against civilians, 
hostage taking and killings continue in the region. There have 
been attempts to involve Russian soldiers and officers carrying 
out a peace-keeping mission in the region to involve in the war. 
  "Especially inadmissible are the facts when representatives 
of the local administrations become organisers of and 
participants in acts of violence. Russian authorities will not 
tolerate glaring violations of human rights and law in the zone 
of the state of emergency," Kostikov said. 
  Calling on the people of North Ossetia and Ingushetia to 
resist provocations of extremists seeking to derail the peace 
process in the region, Russian President Boris Yeltsin stresses 
that law enforcement bodies in the war zone have all necessary 
rights and means to stamp out extremism and protect the 
civilians, Kostikov said. 

</TEXT>

