<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Munitions in Maritime Kray To Be Defused </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Munitions in Maritime Kray To Be Defused </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2405100194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1600 GMT 16 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PM2405100194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast: Announcer-read report over </F>
video of Maritime Kray arms depot explosion aftermath] 
  [Text] The scale of the damage resulting from the 
explosion at the Pacific Fleet's aviation depot has become known 
today. Maritime Kray Governor Yevgeniy Nazdratenko held a 
briefing for journalists. According to his words, more than 
1,500 tonnes of high explosive bombs, missiles of various 
classes, and anti-infantry mines and projectiles went up in the 
air over several hours. A number of projectiles and missiles 
fell on Bolshoy Kamen which is located many kilometers from the 
scene of the explosion. 
  Nazdratenko said that sapper units from the entire Far East 
are being summoned to Maritime Kray to comb through the area and 
defuse munitions which failed to explode. 

</TEXT>

