Daily Report 
<DATE1>  21 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Voronezh Oblast To Accept Tax Payments in Kind </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Voronezh Oblast To Accept Tax Payments in Kind </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2305132794 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 21 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM2305132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Valeriy Mirolevich report: "Taxes To Be Paid to Oblast </F>
Budget in Kind"] 
  [Text] Voronezh -- The reciprocal nonpayments crisis has 
sharply reduced tax revenue to the oblast budget, which is why 
Voronezh Governor A. Kovalev has signed the decree "On Payment 
in Kind of Enterprises' Financial Obligations." 
  Henceforth and until times improve, enterprises, by 
agreement 
with the administration, will pay their taxes in the form of 
their own output. The local authorities intend to use barter to 
acquire the goods which the oblast needs. Enterprises' debts to 
the budget will be considered cleared only after deals have been 
completed by an administrative intermediary. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

