<H3> <TI>   Reportage on UK Foreign Secretary Hurd's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on UK Foreign Secretary Hurd's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Discusses Crimea With Rybkin </H4>

<F P=102> LD2305142794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1400 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 23 May -- "The Crimean issue is too 
important to be used as a card in the presidential election 
campaign in Ukraine." This was said today by Russia's State Duma 
Chairman Ivan Rybkin at a meeting with Douglas Hurd, Britain's 
minister for foreign and Commonwealth affairs [title as 
received]. 
  The speaker of Russia's lower house also said "that 
everything happening in Crimea is Ukraine's internal affair," 
and that "the peoples of the peninsula have the right to 
self-determination, but within the framework of Ukraine and on 
the basis of the principles of the CSCE." 
  Cooperation between the two countries' parliaments was also 
discussed during the meeting. On behalf of the House of 
Commons, Douglas Hurd invited a Duma delegation headed by Ivan 
Rybkin to visit Great Britain this December. 

</TEXT>

