<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official: Russia's Partnership With NATO `Reality' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: Russia's Partnership With NATO `Reality' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305172594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1617 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305172594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia's partnership with NATO is a thing of reality 
despite much propaganda noise about it, the Foreign Minister's 
political adviser Galina Sidorova told Russian reporters in 
Moscow on Monday. 
  She said British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd's visit to 
missile carrying cruiser Admiral Nakhimov at Severomorsk on 
Monday must be seen as one more gesture towards partnership. 
  Sidorova described the Russian-British partnership to this 
end as being significant in a sense. "We have no differences, 
let alone, slightest misunderstanding with Britons. This is 
also indicated by Britain's position on Russia's cooperation 
with the G-7 countries and the Bosnian conflict as well as 
identical approaches to key international issues the two 
countries share", she said. 
  On Sunday's talks in Murmansk between the heads of the 
Russian and British foreign political departments, Sidorova made 
it clear that Britain was keen to see peaceful developments both 
in Crimea and Ukraine. "Britain appears to proceed from the 
principle of not doing harm", she said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

