<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks With Ukraine on Crimea, Black Sea Fleet Open </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Talks With Ukraine on Crimea, Black Sea Fleet Open </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305150994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1454 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305150994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 23 TASS -- The delegations of Russia and 
Ukraine are now meeting in Moscow to discuss the situation in 
the Crimea and the disputed Black Sea Fleet. 
  Opening the talks, Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin 
said that "the problems which have brought us here are very 
difficult." He asked his Ukrainian counterpart Yukhym 
Zvyahilskyy to outline the problems he wants to discuss at the 
talks. Zvyahilskyy named the Black Sea Fleet and the location of 
the Russian part of the fleet as two top priority issues. 
  Before the talks Chernomyrdin and Zvyahilskyy had a 
one-to-one meeting. 
  The talks are also being attended by Ukrainian Vice-Premier 
Valeriy Shmarov, Deputy Foreign Minister Borys Tarasyuk, Deputy 
Defence Minister Ivan Bizhan [name and title as received] and 
Navy commander Vladimir Beskorovainy. The Russian delegation 
includes Deputy Foreign Minister Igor Ivanov, First Deputy 
Defence Minister Boris Gromov [name and title as received] and 
Navy Commander Feliks Gromov. Also taking part are the 
Ukrainian ambassador to Russia and the Russian ambassador to 
Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

