<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- An intermission until 
1400 has been announced in the talks between the heads of 
government of Russia and Ukraine on dividing up the Black Sea 
Fleet and settling the situation in Crimea. 
  Crimean Deputy Prime Minister Yevgeniy Saburov took part in 
today's discussion of the problems of Russian-Ukrainian 
relations, which is into its second day today between 
delegations headed Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin 
and Ukrainian acting Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy. 

</TEXT>

