<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 23 May -- Nikolay Yegorov, the recently 
appointed Russian minister of nationalities, has sent a letter 
to Russian President Boris Yeltsin, calling for the suspension 
of economic sanctions against Abkhazia. In his opinion, the 
conflict in the Abkhazian region has ended as a result of 
documents signed in Moscow on 14 May. 

