<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Meets `Union of 12 December' Members </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Meets `Union of 12 December' Members </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305180994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1715 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 23 May (ITAR-TASS) -- Today in the Kremlin 
Russian President Boris Yeltsin held a meeting with 
representatives of the State Duma deputies' group 
"Liberal-Democratic Union of 12 December," a report by the 
Russian president's press service, circulated here today says. 
The participants in the conversation exchanged opinions on a 
number of topical issues in the country's political and economic 
life and State Duma activities. 
  Assessing the first results of the work of the lower chamber 
of the Russian Federal Assembly, Boris Yeltsin expressed concern 
about its insufficiently high effectiveness. Incidentally, the 
Russian president expressed confidence that the Duma will 
continue to raise the effectiveness of its activities. The 
Russian president stressed that for his part he firmly intends 
to continue the course toward constructive cooperation with the 
Federal Assembly. 
  During the meeting a great deal of attention was paid to a 
package of "economic" decrees signed by the Russian president 
today. Deputies from "the Union of 12 December" expressed their 
support for the measures they contain and that are aimed at the 
further development of economic reforms. 

</TEXT>

