<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Filatov on Yeltsin's Decision To Meet Dudayev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Filatov on Yeltsin's Decision To Meet Dudayev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305135394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1338 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 23 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin's decision to meet with Chechen President Dzhokhar 
Dudayev is based on his concern about the current situation in 
the republic which poses an "increased threat" to its population 
and residents of adjacent regions, including Daghestan and the 
Astrakhan region, Yeltsin's administration chief of staff Sergey 
Filatov said. 
  In an interview with ITAR-TASS on Monday, Filatov said that 
the date of the meeting has yet to be set. 
  Observers believe that Yeltsin had been putting off the 
meeting with Dudayev, waiting for his old foe, former Russian 
parliament chairman Ruslan Khasbulatov to leave the Chechen 
Republic where he stayed after his release from prison under 
amnesty earlier this year. Now that Khasbulatov is in Moscow, 
the last obstacle has been removed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

