<H3> <TI>   ARGUMENTY I FAKTY Most Popular Paper </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ARGUMENTY I FAKTY Most Popular Paper </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205202794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1900 GMT 
22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The weekly ARGUMENTY I FAKTY still remains the most 
popular newspaper in Russia. INTERFAX has received this 
information from the All-Russian Center for the Study of Public 
Opinion. In mid-May the center conducted a poll among 1,600 
people in Russia. This showed that 23 percent of those polled 
always read this weekly. KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA has moved to 
second, while the third spot is held firmly by the SPID-INFO 
magazine, read by 11 percent of those questioned. 

</TEXT>

