<DATE1>  23 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin To Lower Tax Burden on Producers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin To Lower Tax Burden on Producers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305174294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1617 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin has told the 
government to introduce in parliament by September 15 draft laws 
to lower the number of taxes, decrease the level of profit tax 
and VAT by 10 to 20 percent and also the level of taxes related 
to the rate of pay and production. At the same time, his decree 
of May 23 raises the level of tax for individuals as well as for 
the property of individuals and corporate entities. 
  The decree, which aims to limit inflationary processes, 
reduces the number of goods eligible for a special 13 percent 
VAT rate (against the usual 23 percent). 
  From June 1 the rate of payment to the Social Security fund 
will be lowered from 5.4 to 3.4 percent of the sum of charged 
wages. 
  The government is also to adopt a resolution within the next 
two months concerning the possibilities of accelerated 
amortization of capital funds in highly technical branches of 
industry. 
  The decree lays down that production enterprises, the 
foreign 
share of whose capital is no less than 30 percent or 10 million 
dollars and which were registered after January 1, 1994, will 
not have to pay profit tax for the next two years. Profit tax 
in Russia is up to 38 percent. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-63624 </DOCNO>
