<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Edict Lifts Quotas, Licenses on Export Goods, Services </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict Lifts Quotas, Licenses on Export Goods, Services </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305223494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1730 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305223494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 23 May -- The following is the text of an 
edict by the Russian president "on the lifting of quotas and 
licenses on goods and services for export": 
  "To regulate the export of goods and services as well as to 
create equal economic conditions for all parties supplying goods 
beyond Russia's borders, I decree: 
  1. That it be established that from 1 July 1994 quotas and 
licenses for goods and services exported should be applied only 
with regard to those goods and services exported in accordance 
with international obligations of the Russian Federation. 
  2. That the Russian Government should from 1 July 1994 
revoke all privileges with regard to the levying of customs duty 
on exported goods, including budget allocations for the payment 
of customs duty. This applies as well as to the export of goods 
and services for federal and state needs (except for goods 
exported to the countries of the near abroad in accordance with 
inter- governmental agreements). This excludes privileges 
granted in accordance with the Russian law "on customs tariffs," 
the Russian law "on excise duty," and the Russian customs code. 
  3. This decree comes into force from the moment of signing. 
  [Signed] Russian President B. Yeltsin, Moscow, the Kremlin 
  [Dated] 23 May 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

