<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Chernomyrdin Discusses Economic Decrees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Chernomyrdin Discusses Economic Decrees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405125094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1215 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405125094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- At a meeting in the 
Kremlin today Boris Yeltsin and Viktor Chernomyrdin discussed 
the development of mechanisms to implement the latest package of 
presidential decrees on economic issues, aimed at intensifying 
and invigorating the reforms. 
  The Russian president and prime minister considered a number 
of draft decrees on the economy which are under preparation. 
The Russian Federation president's press office told ITAR-TASS 
that personnel issues were also discussed at the meeting. 
  Viktor Chernomyrdin told Boris Yeltsin about the progress in 
talks with Ukraine's acting Prime Minister Yukhym Zvyahilskyy in 
connection with the situation in Crimea. 

</TEXT>

