<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Development of `Smart' Weapons Priority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Development of `Smart' Weapons Priority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2405101594 Moscow SEGODNYA in Russian, 24 May 94, p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK2405101594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow SEGODNYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian, </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [SEGODNYA report: "Russian Military Give Priority to </F>
Re-Armament"] 
  [Text] The Russian Federation Defense Ministry thinks that 
"the program for a scientific-technical head start" in rearming 
the Russian Army should be financed on a priority basis. Andrey 
Kokoshin, first deputy defense minister, told SEGODNYA that 
according to the Defense Ministry's military-technical policy 
approved by the president and the Russian Federation Security 
Council, a special program has been worked out for this purpose. 
It is aimed first of all "at developing smart weapons and means 
of protection from them and also at achieving a high level of 
efficiency of a relatively small, but formidable army," Andrey 
Kokoshin said. To this end, a working group at the Defense 
Ministry's Military-Technical Policy Council has been set up. 
However, according to the working group experts, "its 
implementation is under threat because of the drastic 
deterioration of the situation with defense spending." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

