<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Progress M-23 Docks With Mir Space Complex </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Progress M-23 Docks With Mir Space Complex </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405080694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0710 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405080694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- The Progress M-23 
automatic freight craft docked with the manned Mir space complex 
at 1019 Moscow time today. 
  The freight craft docked with the complex at the Kvant 
module. Fuel for the joint propulsion unit, a reusable ballistic 
capsule, equipment, scientific apparatus, food, and water was 
delivered into orbit. 
  According to telemetric data and reports from cosmonauts 
Viktor Afanasyev, Yuriy Usachev, and Valeriy Polyakov the 
systems on board the orbital complex are working normally. 

</TEXT>

