  [Text] On Sunday evening Azerbaijani formations violated 
the cease-fire accords and from Azerbaijani territory shelled 
Armenian border troop positions near the village of Movses, in 
Armenia's Tauzskiy Rayon. Interfax learned this at the Armenian 
Defense Ministry's press center. There were no casualties, and 
the border troops did not open fire in retaliation. 

