<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Minister Denies Continued Army Attacks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabakh Minister Denies Continued Army Attacks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2305202494 Yerevan SNARK in English 1009 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2305202494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert, May 23 (SNARK)--Arkadi Gukasyan, 
Karabakh Foreign Minister, refuted the statements of the Baku 
officials that the Karabakh Army destroyed the occupied towns, 
villages, communications and historical monuments on the 
threshold of the negotiations on the Karabakh conflict's 
settlement. 
  In his interview to SNARK Mr. Gukasyan said such statements 
aimed at displaying the Karabakh military forces as barbarous in 
the face of the world community. 
  But the fact is that the Azeris themselves have bombarded 
their towns and villages, said the Minister. Only in Agdam 
there fell more than 300 shells since it has been under the 
control of the Karabakh army. 
  Mr. Gukasyan consider the Azeris have shelled their own 
towns 
seeking to destroy the Karabakh military posts and barracks, 
which they suppose are placed there. 
  Now, when the prospects of a long-termed armistice are very 
real, the Azeri propaganda is trying to conceal its own sins and 
to discredit Karabakh, which only complicates the process of 
negotiations, said Arkadi Gukasyan. 

</TEXT>

