<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azeris Accuse Armenia of `Barbaric Acts' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azeris Accuse Armenia of `Barbaric Acts' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305155294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1510 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By Alla Baula, AZERTAC correspondent for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Baku, 23 May (ITAR-TASS) -- "The Armenian armed 
forces are perpetrating barbaric acts in the occupied Azeri 
territories, destroying intact residential buildings, 
communications, health care, economic, and other facilities." 
This statement was made today by Azeri State Adviser Vafa 
Gulizade, who was citing reliable sources. He said this 
information was also confirmed by a deserter from the Armenian 
army. 
  Vafa Gulizade informed journalists that the republic's 
president, Geydar Aliyev, appealed to Jan Eliasson, chairman of 
the CSCE Minsk group, and to permanent members of the CSCE, 
asking them to put pressure on Armenia to end acts of vandalism 
by occupying Armenian troops. In the current situation the 
Azeri president has also written to UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali, asking him to inform members of the UN Security 
Council of these developments. 

</TEXT>

