<H3> <TI>   Christopher Message Supports Government Crimean Stance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Christopher Message Supports Government Crimean Stance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2305145794 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2305145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As has already been reported, in connection with 
the unconstitutional and illegal decisions by the Crimean 
Supreme Soviet regarding the peninsula's status, Ukrainian 
Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko sent letters to foreign 
ministers of other countries and leaders of foreign 
organizations. The international community, alarmed by a 
negative development of events possible in the Crimea, voices 
its unequivocal support for the position expressed in the letter 
by the Ukrainian foreign minister. 
  Anatoliy Zlenko today received William Miller, U.S. 
ambassador to Ukraine, at his request. The American diplomat 
handed over to Mr. Zlenko a personal message from U.S. Secretary 
of State Warren Christopher which, in particular, noted that the 
United States recognizes and highly praises Ukraine's 
responsible and peaceful position on the developments in the 
Crimea. In response to destabilizing processes in the Crimea, 
Ukraine acts according to high principles of the CSCE, with 
which all of us seek to comply. Any other actions could lead to 
confrontation, which would not suit the interests of all sides. 
The United States, the message emphasized, supports the 
sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity of Ukraine 
in its present borders. The United States seeks to expand and 
deepen relations with Ukraine, and would like to move forward 
quickly in assisting Ukraine through economic incentive programs 
that would be useful for the whole country, including the Crimea. 

</TEXT>

