<H3> <TI>   Kiev Did Not Suggest UN Discussion on Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kiev Did Not Suggest UN Discussion on Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305192994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1811 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305192994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukraine has not suggested a UN discussion of the 
Crimean question. This was reported on Monday [23 May] to 
INTERFAX-Ukraine by the head of the information department of 
the Ukrainian Foreign Ministry Yuriy Sergeyev. 
  Commenting on the statement of a political advisor of the 
Russian foreign minister Galina Sidorova that Ukraine wishes the 
Crimean question to be discussed at the UN, Sergeyev expressed 
surprise at how she could have come to such a conclusion. 
  He stressed that the Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoliy 
Zlenko in a letter to the heads of state and leaders of 
international organizations only drew the attention of the world 
public to the complexity of the situation in Crimea. 

</TEXT>

