<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arrival of APC's in Simferopol Said Coincidental </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arrival of APC's in Simferopol Said Coincidental </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305182994 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the press service of the Crimean 
Ministry of Internal Affairs, 29 APCs arrived on Sunday at 
Simferopol train station. After unloading, the APCs headed for 
the territory of the Simferopol military school, escorted by 
Crimean highway inspection officers. 
  Colonel Oleksandr Kostyukov, commander of the National Guard 
brigade, confirmed in an interview for UKRINFORM that the APC's 
did arrive. He said: However, they are not for the military 
school but for our subunits. Their arrival accidentally 
coincided with the developments in the wake of the decision by 
the Crimean Supreme Council session to restore the Constitution 
of 6 May 1993. In reality, it was part of a scheduled process 
of equipping the brigade. 

</TEXT>

