<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Medzhlis Calls for Tatars To Comply With Ukraine Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2305111794 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1000 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2305111794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The political situation in the Crimea has been 
discussed at a meeting held by the medzhlis of the Crimean 
Tatars in Simferopol. A resolution was adopted on the threat of 
an armed conflict in the Crimea. The resolution points out the 
illegal nature of recent edicts issued by the Crimean president 
and Supreme Soviet that are worsening the political situation. 
Due to this, the resolution said, all national representative 
institutions of the Crimean Tatars should comply with the norms 
of international law, the Ukrainian Constitution and its laws, 
and the decisions by the kurultay and the medzhlis of the 
Crimean Tatars. All necessary measures have to be taken to 
prevent our countrymen from getting embroiled in a standoff with 
the Ukrainian state, the resolution by the medzhlis of the 
Crimean Tatars stated. 

</TEXT>

