<H3> <TI>   Crimea Tense But Calm; Ukrainian Reinforcements Arrive </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimea Tense But Calm; Ukrainian Reinforcements Arrive </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405083194 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The situation in Crimea is largely calm, RIA was 
told by (Petr Chernichevich), an advisor to the Crimean 
president on military issues. However, he said that some 
tension could nevertheless be sensed, caused by the 
unpredictability of the Ukrainian authorities' next moves. 
  Reinforcements are constantly arriving at the Ukrainian 
National Guard units in Simferopol and Sevastopol. The number 
of guards has already reached 2,000, consisting mainly of men 
from western Ukraine who arrived in Simferopol on Sunday. They 
have also received 29 armored personnel carriers, according to 
Chernichevich. 
  All important sites in the Crimean capital remain under the 
strict guard of interior troop units loyal to the Crimean 
Government, and the city's streets are being patrolled by 
Crimean Cossacks. 

</TEXT>

