<H3> <TI>   Nationalists Demand Annulment of Crimean Autonomy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Nationalists Demand Annulment of Crimean Autonomy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105111694 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1000 GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Congress of Ukrainian Nationalists believes the 
Ukrainian president and Supreme Council should introduce 
presidential rule in Crimea and repeal its autonomous status. 
This was said in a statement the congress made regarding the 
latest developments in Crimea. The document stresses that the 
Crimean Supreme Council's decision to restore the autonomy's 
constitution in its original version represents disregard for 
the fundamental law of Ukraine and international agreements on 
the inviolability of the borders and territorial integrity of 
states. The statement's authors describe these actions as 
criminal in respect of the Ukrainian people and state. 
  The Congress of Ukrainian Nationalists also demands that the 
registration in Crimea of political parties, which perform 
anti-Ukrainian activity, should be discontinued, separatism 
ended, and calm and peaceful work guaranteed for the peninsula's 
citizens. 

</TEXT>

