<H3> <TI>   New Data Transmission Network Introduced 20 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Data Transmission Network Introduced 20 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2305134394 Tallinn BNS in English 1638 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2305134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Baltic Business Weekly" feature] </F>
  [Text] Public data transmission network, DataLatvija, was 
introduced May 20 in Latvia. The new network will allow Latvian 
enterprises, state institutions, banks, border guards, customs 
and inhabitants to transmit quickly and qualitatively data to 
subscribers and customers in Latvia and abroad. 
  Presently, DataLatvija consists of three primary network 
exchanges in Riga, Rezekne and Ventspils. The network will be 
extended in future and it will include all Latvia's districts. 
  The installation of the above mentioned service costs 150 
lats, and subscription for a month costs from 15 to 25 lats. 

</TEXT>

