<H3> <TI>   Slezevicius Sums up Results of Visit To France </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Slezevicius Sums up Results of Visit To France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305191294 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 
1300 GMT 1300 GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network </F>
<F P=105>  Lithuanian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] France understands ever better Lithuania's economic 
and political aims and is determined to support them by every 
means. This was said by Prime Minister Adolfas Slezevicius after 
his visit to France. 
  According to him, his meetings with the French president, 
the 
head of the government, some members of the Cabinet of 
Ministers, and representatives of influential financial and 
trading companies, demonstrated there was a great interest in 
Lithuania and in the possibilities of political and economic 
cooperation. This cooperation, claims Adolfas Slezevicius, 
should become concrete now. 
  As is known, the Lithuanian delegation led by Adolfas 
Slezevicius paid a working visit to Paris on 17-21 May. 
  The Lithuanian prime minister mentioned the European 
stability pact as one of the most important facts of political 
support. Adolfas Slezevicius has an especially favorable opinion 
about the initiative by the French prime minister to hold 
regional round tables where it will be possible to discuss at 
the level of European state leaders and experts, for example, 
relations between the Baltic states and Russia. This will 
divert our dialogue with Russia in a completely different 
direction, claims Adolfas Slezevicius. 
  It is especially important to Lithuania in the sense of 
economic cooperation to attract as much French capital as 
possible to Lithuania. Some conditions are essential for this 
purpose, for instance, the protection of and guarantees to 
investments, insurance, the abolition of double taxation, etc. 
  According to Adolfas Slezevicius, expert missions from 
French 
insurance companies, the Central Bank, the Finance Ministry, and 
the electronic industry, will soon be coming to Lithuania. 
Concrete projects in which French companies could take part 
will be discussed. Technical assistance is possible in the 
administration of taxes and in financial payments. 

</TEXT>

