<H3> <TI>   Reportage on UK Foreign Secretary Hurd's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on UK Foreign Secretary Hurd's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Meets With Chernomyrdin on Economic Issues </H4>

<F P=102> LD2405085594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0810 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405085594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian Prime Minister 
Viktor Chernomyrdin and Douglas Hurd, British secretary of state 
for foreign and Commonwealth affairs, discussed mainly economic 
issues at a meeting this morning. 
  Viktor Chernomyrdin informed the British minister about the 
package of decrees on stepping up structural transformations in 
the Russian economy, which were prepared by the government and 
signed by President Boris Yeltsin Monday. They are designed, in 
particular, to optimize the government's taxation policy and 
attract foreign and Russian capital investments. 
  Douglas Hurd, for his part, noted that after meeting with 
British businessmen in Moscow he arrived at the conclusion that 
business people in his country take an extremely optimistic view 
with regard to the prospects for economic cooperation between 
Russia and Britain. Douglas Hurd confirmed the invitation given 
by British Prime Minister John Major to Viktor Chernomyrdin to 
visit London officially at the end of 1994 or the beginning of 
1995. 

</TEXT>

