<H3> <TI>   UK's Hurd To Discuss Crimea With President Kravchuk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UK's Hurd To Discuss Crimea With President Kravchuk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305125594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1104 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The brief meeting between Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk and British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd in Kiev on 
Tuesday [24 May] will focus on settlement of the Crimean issue. 
This was said by Hurd himself in an interview with INTERFAX in 
Murmansk. 
  Hurd suggested that this issue must be considered within the 
scope of development of friendly relations between Great Britain 
and Ukraine. Hurd recommended that talks on Crimea be held in 
the presence of the Russian party which could contribute to 
better understanding between Kiev and Simferopol through its 
calm and constructive participation. "We hope that both parties 
are reasonable enough to solve the problem by peaceful methods," 
Hurd said. 

</TEXT>

