<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Returns From New York </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Returns From New York </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN2205172194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1655 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2205172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 22 May (INA)--Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 
'Aziz returned to Baghdad from New York this evening. 
  During his visit to the United Nations, Tariq 'Aziz held 
extensive consultations with the ambassadors of the Security 
Council's member states, particularly those of the permanent 
member states, on the economic blockade imposed on Iraq. 
  Tariq 'Aziz also met with the Austrian foreign minister in 
Vienna on his way to New York. 

</TEXT>

