<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma for Increasing Defense Spending </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma for Increasing Defense Spending </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505091594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0825 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 25 May (Business-TASS) -- The State Duma 
committee on economic policy has spoken in favor of increasing 
Russia's military expenditure in 1994 to up to 55 trillion 
rubles, thus supporting the Duma's defense committee on this. 
If the State Duma were to approve this initiative during the 
debates of the budget in its second reading, the overall 
increase for national defense would exceed the original sum by 
17.9 trillion rubles. The proposal to increase Russia's 
military expenditure to up to 55 trillion rubles was supported 
by Russian President Boris Yeltsin. 

</TEXT>

