<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Investigates Votes Approving New Constitution </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Investigates Votes Approving New Constitution </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505103994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0829 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505103994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 25 May -- The State Duma has today 
instructed the Credentials Commission of the Duma to verify the 
authenticity of reports in some of the mass media saying that a 
number of electoral associations that now have factions 
represented in the Duma used funds for their election campaign, 
which were received from abroad. In addition, the Credentials 
Commission of the State Duma has been instructed to elucidate 
whether there is any truth in reports saying that not enough of 
the electorate voted for the adoption of the new Russian 
Constitution. The commission must provide its response to these 
issues in two weeks. 

</TEXT>

