<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 24 May, TASS -- "Talks with the parliamentary 
delegation from the Republic of Crimea are proceeding in a 
normal and constructive manner. The Ukrainian side is satisfied 
with the proceedings," Ukrainian Parliament delegation leader 
Boris Oleynik told ITAR-TASS. 
  Crimean parliamentarians refused to comment. 
  The meeting continues behind closed doors. 

</TEXT>

