agriculture minister and member of the Peasants Party, was 
elected first deputy speaker of the Ukrainian parliament at a 
closed plenary sitting of the Supreme Council this evening. 
Oleh Demin, an independent, and vice president of the 
Ukrainian-Siberian investment corporation, was elected deputy 
speaker. 

