<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Edict on Export of Arms, Associated Services </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Edict on Export of Arms, Associated Services </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2405131594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 24 May 94 
p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM2405131594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Government Decree No. 479 "On Giving </F>
Enterprises the Right To Participate in the Russian Federation's 
Military-Technical Cooperation With Foreign Countries," dated 
Moscow, 6 May 1994, and signed by Russian Federation Government 
Chairman V. Chernomyrdin] 
  [Text] In order to raise the efficiency of the Russian 
Federation's military-technical cooperation with foreign 
countries, the Russian Federation Government decrees: 
  1. To ratify the Statute on the Attestation and Registration 
of Enterprises, giving them the right to carry out exports of 
weapons and military hardware and of military work and services, 
and put it into effect as of 1 May 1994. 
  2. To give enterprises which develop and manufacture weapons 
and military hardware and are attested and registered as 
participants in foreign economic activity in the sphere of 
military-technical cooperation, the following rights: 
  to seek out foreign clients in countries with which 
military-technical cooperation is not prohibited, to carry out 
demonstrations and, during talks, to give the tactical and 
technical specifications of weapons and military hardware whose 
export is authorized, to announce the guideline price agreed 
according to the established procedure, and to conduct 
advertising work and other marketing work; 
  to sign contracts and, on the basis of licenses obtained 
according to the established procedure, to independently export 
weapons and military hardware they have manufactured over and 
above the state defense order, as well as military work and 
services; 
  to select agents from among the organizations which have 
obtained, according to the established procedure, permits to 
conduct foreign economic activity in the sphere of 
military-technical cooperation. 
  3. As a partial amendment to Point 3 of the Statute on the 
Procedure for Licensing the Export and Import of Military Output 
(Work, Services) on the Territory of the Russian Federation, 
ratified by decree No. 80 of the Russian Federation Council of 
Ministers-Government dated 28 January 1993 (SOBRANIYE AKTOV 
PREZIDENTA I PRAVITELSTVA ROSSIYSKOY FEDERATSII, 1993, No. 6, p 
484), to prescribe that the export of spare parts, training 
equipment, and accessories for weapons and military hardware 
earlier supplied to foreign countries, and also the carrying out 
of work as part of their technical servicing and repair 
(including the use of series-produced subassemblies to replace 
those that have been taken out of production) is carried out 
without the formulation of a Russian Federation Government 
decision. 
  [signed] Russian Federation Government Chairman V. 
Chernomyrdin 

</TEXT>

