<H3> <TI>   Kolesnikov Questions Proliferation of Armed Formations </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kolesnikov Questions Proliferation of Armed Formations </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2405141994 Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA in Russian 24 May 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2405141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KOMSOMOLSKAYA PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Why Does Russia Need 4 Million Men?"] </F>
  [Text] Colonel General Mikhail Kolesnikov, chief of the 
Russian Federation Armed Forces General Staff, stated at a 
closed session of the State Duma Defense Committee that "a 
multiplication of power structures is now going on in Russia." 
In fact over 4 million people (2.3 million in the Armed Forces) 
have been put "under arms" in the country. 
  Besides the Army and Internal Troops, Mobile Troops are 
being 
formed. The Ministry for Emergency Situations is planning to 
form its own navy. Military formations are being recreated 
within the Federal Counterintelligence Service system and in the 
Federal Government Communications Service. The president's 
Security Service is being expanded. 
  Kolesnikov said that Russia "is not in a position to 
maintain 
four armies." He stated that the Russian Federation Defense 
Ministry is ready, "should the government so decide," to 
transfer the Russian Federation Navy and part of the Airborne 
Forces to the Border Guard Troops' command in order to form 
mobile forces." According to Kolesnikov, because of insufficient 
resources, this is the fourth year that mobilization assemblies 
have not been carried out and all large-scale exercises have 
been scrapped (all that is left is command and staff map 
exercises). 
  Given normal financing, Kolesnikov said, we would be able to 
reduce the Army to 1.5 million men as early as this year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

