<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Addressing a conference entitled "New Aspects of 
Reforming Russian Economy" in Moscow, Aleksandr Khandruyev, 
deputy chairman of the [Russian] Central Bank, vehemently 
opposed the transformation of the Russian Central Bank into a 
U.S.-style federal reserve system. 
  Such a system cannot be imposed on to Russian realities in 
its existing form, and neither can any other model, he stressed. 

