<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Signs Law Concerning Military Badges, Rank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Signs Law Concerning Military Badges, Rank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405191194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1405 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405191194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 24 May -- Russian President Yeltsin has 
signed a decree "on the military uniform and badges of military 
rank." 
  With this document, in accordance with Article 38 of the 
Russian Federation law "On Military Duty and Military Service," 
Yeltsin has confirmed the uniform and badges of rank of 
servicemen of the armed forces of the Russian Federation and 
other troops, organs of external intelligence, 
counterintelligence, the chief directorate for protection and 
the security service of the president. 
  ITAR-TASS has been told by the president's press service 
that 
the Russian Government has also been instructed to confirm 
within three months regulations governing the provision of 
soldier's supplies and standard quantities for the supply of 
items. 
  Yeltsin decreed that the corresponding decrees of the 
Presidium of the USSR Supreme Soviet, concerning servicemen's 
badges of rank, be considered inoperative. 

</TEXT>

