<H3> <TI>   Official Says Belarus in No Hurry To Join NATO's PFP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Says Belarus in No Hurry To Join NATO's PFP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405180694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1617 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405180694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belarusian Deputy Foreign Minister Petr Belyayev 
announced that his republic's possible participation in NATO's 
Partnership for Peace [PFP] program would not be analyzed before 
presidential elections and the autumn parliamentary session. 
  In his opinion, politically, Belarus was ready to join this 
project, and had informed the NATO leadership. 
  In an interview with INTERFAX, Belyayev said that the search 
for his republic's possible participation in NATO's program was 
very difficult, because Belarus had not yet reorganized its 
armed forces due to the deteriorating economic situation. 
  Belarus must not hasten to join the Partnership for Peace 
program, because it was faced with many problems in conventional 
and strategic disarmament. 

</TEXT>

