<H3> <TI>   Russia Owed 6 Trillion Belarusian Rubles for Fuel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Owed 6 Trillion Belarusian Rubles for Fuel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405134094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1314 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by BELINFORM correspondent Yekaterina Vysotskaya for </F>
TASS] 
  [Text] Minsk 24 May TASS -- As of today the Republic of 
Belarus has to pay six trillion Belarusian roubles to Russia for 
fuel resources it has already used. But energy consumers alone 
owe one trillion 200 billion, and 4.2 trillion hang in mid-air. 
  Commenting on the situation, National Bank of Belarus Board 
of Directors Chairman Stanislav Bogdankevich said: "We bought it 
cheap, sold cheap, and are living well. All this for the sake 
of supporting industry, in order to reduce the cost of 
production. But this has led us into a blind alley, because if 
the consumption of power is not cut down, and one has to pay, 
then after all it must be recovered from someone." 
  The chief treasurer of the republic noted that an idea is 
already wandering, according to which the national bank will 
have to "create out of air" 4 trillion and pay up. "But the way 
this question is formulated is devoid of common sense," he 
emphasised. 

</TEXT>

