<H3> <TI>   Deputies Call for UN `Evaluation' of Monetary Merger </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputies Call for UN `Evaluation' of Monetary Merger </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2405135794 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1230 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2405135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A group of people's deputies from the Belarusian 
Social Democratic Assembly faction in the Supreme Soviet has 
addressed Matthew Kahane, UN permanent representative to the 
Republic of Belarus, with a letter regarding the violation of 
the Belarusian Constitution by Prime Minister Vyachaslaw Kebich. 
In particular, the letter broaches the agreement on monetary 
merger between Belarus and Russia, which was signed by the prime 
minister. "Mr. Kebich, resting upon those forces in the Supreme 
Soviet, which allow themselves to grossly violate the state 
constitutional system, attempts to incorporate Belarus into the 
Russian Federation by an unconstitutional means," the letter 
reads. "We are also astonished by the position of the Russian 
Government, a permanent member of the UN Security Council, which 
signed the agreement contradicting the Belarusian Constitution." 
The authors of the letter express their assurance that the 
international community is not interested in destabilizing the 
situation and maintaining Russian nuclear weapons in the center 
of Europe; therefore, the United Nations will give a legal 
evaluation of the above mentioned agreement as well as the 
resolution on the holding of presidential elections in May-June 
1994. 

</TEXT>

