  [Text] The next round of Russian-Belarusian talks on the 
issues of military cooperation has ended in Minsk. According to 
Veniyamin Popov, head of the Russian delegation, Russia will be 
given the possibility to use the radio station in Vileyka even 
after the completion of strategic forces' withdrawal from 
Belarus. In addition, the construction of a missile warning 
radar system near Baranovichi will be completed. This facility 
will also remain on Belarusian territory after the year of 2000 
and will operate in the interests of all the countries which are 
the members to the treaty on collective security. 

