<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 24 May (AFP) -- Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk will travel to Luxembourg next month to sign a 
partnership and cooperation agreement with the European Union, 
deputy foreign minister Alexander Makarenko said Tuesday [24 
May]. 
  Makarenko told AFP that Kravchuk would visit Luxembourg on 
12-14 June. 
  The Foreign Ministry official said that British Foreign 
Secretary Douglas Hurd, currently visiting Kiev, told him that 
Ukraine's closer ties with the EU would "create a different 
political climate." 
  Hurd said that member-states of the EU would guarantee the 
territorial integrity and sovereignty of Ukraine, Makarenko said. 

