<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "A Statement at the Ukrainian-Russian </F>
Border"] 
  [Text] Representatives of the command of Ukrainian and the 
Russian Federation's troops, Customs services of the two states, 
leadership of the ministries of internal affairs, and state 
administrations of Kharkiv and Belgorod oblasts met with 
journalists at the Ukrainian-Russian border. As is known, after 
signing the memorandum on border cooperation between Ukraine and 
Russia, some mass media disseminated a "sensation" on the 
renewal of the system of single borders of the CIS countries. 
It was stressed at the news conference that Ukraine and the 
Russian Federation are building their relations on the 
principles of friendship and good-neighborly relations and do 
not intend to violate the sovereign rights of the close 
neighbor. Each side strives to respect each other's state 
attributes, including state borders. 

