<H3> <TI>   Discuss Reform Process </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discuss Reform Process </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2405192094 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1750 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2405192094 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 23/5/1994 -- "We are aware that 
the responsibility for a successful implementation of economic 
reforms was assumed by the top leadership and first of all by 
the head of state which accepted us as co-authors of the reform 
program," declared today at a meeting with President Snegur the 
vice-president of the World Bank (WB), Welfred Thaiwitz, reports 
a presidential press service communique. The WB will continue 
to support financially reforms in Moldova. The WB experts say 
that some progress has already been registered: stability of 
national currency and decrease in the inflation rates. 
President Snegur welcomed the WB's idea of opening a permanent 
mission in Moldova and expressed his hope that the latter, 
together with the IMF, will contribute to economic recovery. 
Snegur mentioned two aspects of major importance for a 
successful implementation of reforms -- political stability and 
rapid privatization of state property. It was specified that 
the Ministry of Privatization, which was recently created, was 
meant to serve as a catalyst for the process, to make it 
consistent and irreversible, says the press communique. 

</TEXT>

