<HT>    "drsov101_h_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-101 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  23 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Socialist Leader Criticizes Snegur for Joining PDAM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socialist Leader Criticizes Snegur for Joining PDAM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2405185594 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1750 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2405185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau BASAPRESS, 23/5/1994 -- President Mircea 
Snegur's decision to join the governing party, the Agrarian 
Democratic Party of Moldova [PDAM], reveals unsteadiness in his 
political views, declared to BASA Valentin Krylov, a leader of 
the Socialist Party. According to Krylov, previously, President 
Snegur declared that the president should be above any party's 
interests. "It might seem that the president has changed his 
political views, thought it is possible that he follows two 
objectives: to give more strength to the PDAM before local 
elections and to prepare to run as an agrarian for President in 
1996, which are expected to be multi-party," said Krylov, 
mentioning that "today it is not too early to consider the next 
presidential elections and the PDAM will gain much strength from 
Snegur's membership." 

</TEXT>

