<F P=103> NC2405160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku AZERTAC </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, 23 May (AZERTAC)--Today, State Adviser of 
Azerbaijan Mr. Vafa Gulizadeh has made a statement, which says 
that the Armenian armed forces are committing barbarian actions 
on the occupied Azeri territory destroying dwelling houses, 
communications and agricultural installations. According to V. 
Gulizadeh, this information has been confirmed by a deserter 
from the Armenian Army. The deserter said that the Armenians 
committed those actions since they knew that they would soon 
leave the occupied Azeri territory. 
  V. Gilizadeh has also said that the Azerbaijani President 
Geydar Aliyev appealed to the Chairman of the CSCE's Minsk Group 
J. Eliasson and regular member states of the CSCE with a request 
to bring pressure to bear upon Armenia to stop committing 
barbarian actions on the Azeri territory. The President Aliyev 
has also appealed to the UN Secretary General Mr. Butrus-Ghali 
and asked him to inform the members of the UN Security Council 
about these crimes committed by Armenians. The state adviser 
thinks that the world community must pay attention to the 
felonies committed by the Armenian armed forces and take 
measures in order to stop barbarian actions. 

</TEXT>

