<H3> <TI>   Brazauskas Sends Telegram to Newly Elected German President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Brazauskas Sends Telegram to Newly Elected German President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2505093694 Vilnius ELTA in English 2039 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2505093694 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius ELTA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News Bulletin" No. 506] </F>
  [Text] Vilnius, 24 May, ELTA -- President Algirdas 
Brazauskas sent on Tuesday [24 May] a congratulation telegram to 
the newly elected President of Germany Roman Herzog. 
  "I would like to take this opportunity to convey my 
heartfelt 
congratulations on the victory in the elections of the president 
for the first time held in the unified Germany. I earnestly 
hope the relations between our two countries will further expand 
under Your Excellency's good offices. I wish you success and 
the best of luck," Brazauskas said in his telegram. 
  Brazauskas also sent a telegram to the former German 
President Richard von Weizsacker. He said in it: "On the 
occasion, I would like to thank you for the attention and 
understanding shown to our state. 
  ``Germany, one of the largest European states, did not 
refuse 
to help Lithuania during the crucial historical period. Traces 
of your last-year visit in Lithuania have remained significant 
in strengthening the democracy, tolerance, mutual understanding 
of various nations. 
  ``I am sure the newly elected President Roman Herzog will be 
a worthy successor and relations between Lithuania and Germany 
will be further developed. 
  ``I hope you will not forget Lithuania in future. Therefore, 
I would like to invite you as my personal guest to visit our 
country once more,'' Brazauskas said. 

</TEXT>

