<F P=100> RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Salvation Front Calls for Protection of Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Salvation Front Calls for Protection of Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405113894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1051 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405113894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Political Council of the National Salvation 
Front (NSF) called on its supporters, the State Duma and all 
public leaders and political parties to avoid moves that could 
lead to the betrayal of Crimea and to work to protect the 
Crimean republic and Crimean Constitution. 
  The NSF Political Council said a dramatic conflict was about 
to erupt in Crimea and the Ukrainian leaders would be to blame 
for it. The Crimeans' quest for the protection of the age-long 
ties with Russia have been threatened by Kiev, the Council said. 
  The Russian president and government were equally 
responsible 
for what was happening on the peninsula. Now that Ukraine was 
running up an enormous debt to Russia, the NSF Council said, the 
Russian leaders could resort to absolutely reliable and peaceful 
means of averting violence in Crimea. 
  The NSF Council declared the Crimean developments to be a 
test of the patriotic declarations made by many local political 
parties and movements. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
