<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 24 TASS -- A document relating to the 
division of the Black Sea Fleet between Russia and Ukraine is 
being prepared for signing after the current talks between the 
heads of government of two republics. 
  The document will be signed by Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin and Ukraine's Acting Premier Yukhym Zvyahilskyy 
after all points are agreed between the two delegations. 
  The joint document will contain specific terms and 
conditions 
of the division of the Black Sea Fleet's infrastructure and of 
the bases of the two national fleets. 
  A press conference will be held after the signing. 

