<F P=100> RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Wants Ukraine Navy Moved From Sevastopol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Wants Ukraine Navy Moved From Sevastopol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405164194 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1551 GMT 
24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405164194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia is proposing to make Sevastopol the main base 
for the Russian part of the Black Sea Fleet and to relocate the 
Ukrainian navy outside of the town. Options include having the 
Ukraine navy stationed in Balaklava, in Crimea, or in Odessa. 
Our correspondent was told this by unofficial sources. Those 
unofficial sources think that a final document may be signed 
this evening. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

