<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Talks Adjourned Until 25 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Black Sea Fleet Talks Adjourned Until 25 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405194594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1845 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 May -- Talks between the heads of 
government of Russia and Ukraine on settling the problems of the 
Black Sea Fleet have been adjourned until tomorrow. A decision 
to do so was taken late this evening by members of the 
delegations of the two countries. 
  The sides were unable to reach agreement on a number of 
points while working out an intergovernmental document dividing 
the Black Sea Fleet. 
  The talks will be continued tomorrow with the same people 
taking part. 
  Valeriy Shmarov, deputy prime minister of Ukraine, told 
journalists that the positions of the sides undoubtedly came 
closer together during today's talks, but there are still a 
great many unresolved problems. At the same time he confirmed 
the desire of the Ukrainian side to reach an agreement. 

</TEXT>

