<H3> <TI>   Grachev: Russia To Sign NATO Partnership Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev: Russia To Sign NATO Partnership Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405154494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1442 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405154494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 24h May -- Russia's Defense Minister Pavel 
Grachev arrived in Brussels today where he will make a report on 
the new Russian defense doctrine to the NATO leadership and the 
defense ministers of the alliance countries this evening. 
  He was met by Belgian Defense Minister Leo Delcroix and by 
other officials at Melsbroek military airport. 
  Replying to journalists' questions, P. Grachev said that 
Russia will sign a framework document of the NATO "Partnership 
for Peace" program at the same time as an agreement on bilateral 
cooperation between Russia and NATO when this agreement is 
finally ready. 

</TEXT>

