<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpts] Yet another extremely important subject today is 
the NATO defense ministers conference in Brussels. [passage 
omitted] 
  [Correspondent K. Mazheyka] At this moment, as you are 
watching this report, Defense Minister Pavel Grachev, who 
arrived in Brussels an hour ago, is setting out our conception 
of partnership. 
  [Begin Grachev recording] I have simply brought Russia's 
vision of the Partnership for Peace. The first section is 
political partnership. The second section is military 
partnership, and the third section is a miscellaneous one. 
These are the specifically worked out parameters of our 
partnership. We shall propose that our representatives and the 
special representatives of the NATO countries draw up a 
broad-scale agreement. When it is ready, we will sign two 
documents: a general conception of the partnership and the 
agreement that will be drawn up if the NATO members accept it. 
