<H3> <TI>   Discusses Cooperation With NATO </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Cooperation With NATO </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505085494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0803 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Aleksandr Mineyev and </F>
Vladimir Smelov] 
  [Text] Brussels, 25 May -- The reaction of the U.S. defense 
secretary to the Russian concept of wider cooperation with NATO 
was "noncommittal," Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev told 
ITAR-TASS after meeting his U.S. counterpart William Perry at 
the NATO Headquarters. 
  "It seems, the Russian minister added, that this is linked 
to 
the fact that the American side is not yet familiar with the 
main parameters of our proposals on this. They will be handed 
over to NATO's acting secretary general today." 
  In P. Grachev's words, the meeting which lasted for over an 
hour discussed primarily issues of bilateral interaction. "Our 
cooperation is growing stronger by the day and we are finding 
more and more mutual understanding," he stressed. 

</TEXT>

