<F P=100> RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Plan Defining PFP Participation Submitted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Plan Defining PFP Participation Submitted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2505102594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0928 
GMT 25 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2505102594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 25 May -- The Russian side today submitted 
to NATO a document containing the main parameters of Russian 
participation in the implementation of the Partnership for Peace 
program. At the same time it was proposed to start drawing up a 
broad program of cooperation between Russia and NATO that would 
be based on these parameters and to sign the outline document as 
soon as this program is ready. 
  In the political sphere, Russia proposes the creation of an 
effective mechanism of mutual consultations on the entire range 
of problems of European and world security, which would operate 
both on a regular basis and in emergencies. Such a mechanism 
would be a practical step on the way to the formation of a 
long-term system of collective security and stability in Europe 
under the aegis of the CSCE. In the military sphere, Russia is 
ready to develop cooperation with NATO and partners in such 
areas as coordinating joint military activities, peace-keeping, 
transparency in military planning and military activities, and 
personnel training. It also expects to establish partnership 
relations in other areas, such as disarmament and arms control, 
conversion, nonproliferation of mass destruction weapons, and 
protection of the environment. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

