<H3> <TI>   U.S. Mission's Far Eastern Tour Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Mission's Far Eastern Tour Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2405114294 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 24 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2405114294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [ITAR-TASS report: "A Find for America"] </F>
  [Text] Russia is being sold both wholesale and retail. 
Presently this is an open secret. Yet another news agency 
report has only proved the point. 
  The U.S. government's private investment corporation has 
started a search for Far Eastern regions that are most promising 
in terms of investment. Yesterday, the Americans visited the 
free economic zone at Nakhodka, where they examined its ports 
and enterprises. 
  The U.S. mission will also visit Khabarovsk Kray, Sakhalin, 
and Kamchatka. After the tour, the mission chief, U.S. Senator 
Ruth Harkin, said they will give recommendations to her 
country's entrepreneurs as to which regions of the Russian Far 
East are best for investment. She called Nakhodka one of Russia 
's most promising areas at this stage. 

</TEXT>

