<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev: No Withdrawal From Estonia Until Issue Resolved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev: No Withdrawal From Estonia Until Issue Resolved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405120494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1122 
GMT 24 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2405120494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Dmitriy Chubarov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 24 May (ITAR-TASS) -- "We will not withdraw 
our troops from Estonia until the issue of the retired 
servicemen is resolved in a civilized fashion," Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev said today before flying to Tallinn. He 
was going to Estonia to take part in a ministerial session of 
the Council of Baltic Sea States. The Russian minister also 
intends holding a series of meetings with Estonian leaders. 
  According to the Russian foreign minister, discussion of the 
Tartu treaty [signed by Estonia and Russia in 1920, dealing with 
territorial issues] is pointless. "We do not intend to discuss 
any territorial claims," the minister noted. 
  Touching on the situation in Crimea, A. Kozyrev stressed 
that 
the main thing now is to refrain from using force. Talks 
between Russia and Ukraine on this issue are continuing at this 
time. 

</TEXT>

