<H3> <TI>   Federation Council Official Receives Slovak Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Federation Council Official Receives Slovak Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405110994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1049 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405110994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Lyudmila Yermakova] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 24 TASS -- Neither the State Duma nor 
the Federation Council will impede the ratification of the 
treaty between the Russian Federation and the Slovak Republic, 
Federation Council Deputy Chairman Valerian Viktorov told a 
parliamentary delegation from the Slovak Republic during their 
meeting in the Russian parliament today. 
  According to Viktorov, the Russian Foreign Ministry has 
already sent the document to the State Duma, the lower chamber 
of the Russian federal legislature, for consideration. 
  Slovak delegation leader Ivan Laluga said members of the new 
Slovak parliament, which has been functioning for a mere six 
months, are interested primarily in the democratization process 
in Russia and in principles of work of the Federation Council in 
this respect. He said Slovakia is considering the establishment 
of a second chamber in its parliament to better reflect the 
interests of the regions". 
  The sides exchanged views on the activity of legislatures in 
the two countries and expressed confidence that their inter- 
parliamentary ties will continue to strengthen. 
  Responding to questions about relations between the Russian 
Federation and the Chechen Republic, Viktorov stressed that "all 
problems between the federal centre and the Chechen Republic 
must be settled though negotiations". According to him, it is 
far from best to try and solve such problems by force. He said 
the Russian president's intention to meet with the president of 
the Chechen Republic was a positive development. 

</TEXT>

