<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Bank Declares `Little Hare' Only Legal Currency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Bank Declares `Little Hare' Only Legal Currency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2405180994 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1706 GMT 24 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2405180994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The National Bank of Belarus (NBB) has declared the 
Belarusian payment coupon (nicknamed "zaichik", or "little 
hare") the only legal tender in the Republic from 1 June until 
the moment the agreement on monetary unification with Russia 
comes into force. 
  The NBB told INTERFAX that it had made the decision "in view 
of the amount of time it is taking to unify the monetary systems 
of Russia and Belarus and the fact that the current state of 
confusion regarding payments cannot be allowed to continue." 
According to the NBB decision, all accounting in Belarus will 
be carried out only in the payment coupons until the monetary 
union officially takes place and all commercial organizations 
must convert their assets from Russian rubles to "zaichiki" at 
the official NBB exchange rate (10.5 to the Russian rubles on 24 
May) within the shortest period of time. 
  The NBB will set a special exchange rate every week for 
operations not involving trade and charges for services 
(especially transport and communications). 

</TEXT>

