<F P=100> RUSSIAN INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Swedish Aide: `Too Many Military' in Kaliningrad Oblast </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Swedish Aide: `Too Many Military' in Kaliningrad Oblast </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2405124794 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 24 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2405124794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Valeriy Gromak report: "Officers Seem To Have Chance to </F>
Study in Sweden"] 
  [Text] Kaliningrad -- Swedish Foreign Minister Baroness 
Margaretha af Ugglas is here on a familiarization visit. The 
baroness met with Yuriy Matochkin, head of the Kaliningrad 
Oblast Administration, visited the Kaliningrad International 
Business School, toured the city, laid wreaths at the tomb of 
the German philosopher Kant and the Pushkin Memorial, and met 
with journalists. The Swedish foreign minister believes that 
Kaliningrad Oblast has too many military personnel, and Sweden 
is prepared to help retrain officers being discharged into the 
reserve. 

</TEXT>

